<header class="ptm-atrium-head">
  <p class="ptm-eyebrow">An exhibit · rooms about perception</p>
  <h1 class="ptm-title">Perceptionarium</h1>
  <p class="ptm-lede">A wandered exhibit. Each room is a small staging of something your nervous system is already doing without telling you. The rooms don&rsquo;t add anything to the world; they point at processes that have been running the whole time, and name them.</p>
  <p class="ptm-meta">No required order. Headphones recommended in some rooms.</p>
</header>

<nav class="ptm-rooms" aria-label="Available rooms">

  <a class="ptm-room is-live" href="/perceptionarium/prison-pink/">
    <span class="ptm-room-num">01</span>
    <span class="ptm-room-body">
      <span class="ptm-room-title">Prison pink</span>
      <span class="ptm-room-sub">A color that was supposed to calm violent prisoners. A claim that didn&rsquo;t replicate. An afterimage that always does.</span>
      <span class="ptm-room-tags"><em>color science</em> · <em>opponent process</em> · <em>replication crisis</em></span>
    </span>
    <span class="ptm-room-state">enter ›</span>
  </a>

  <div class="ptm-room is-scaffold" aria-disabled="true">
    <span class="ptm-room-num">02</span>
    <span class="ptm-room-body">
      <span class="ptm-room-title">Voyager</span>
      <span class="ptm-room-sub">Recordings of plasma waves around Jupiter, made by a probe now twenty-four light-hours away.</span>
      <span class="ptm-room-tags"><em>space physics</em> · <em>auditory threat circuitry</em></span>
    </span>
    <span class="ptm-room-state">scaffold</span>
  </div>

  <div class="ptm-room is-scaffold" aria-disabled="true">
    <span class="ptm-room-num">03</span>
    <span class="ptm-room-body">
      <span class="ptm-room-title">Pulsars</span>
      <span class="ptm-room-sub">A neutron star spinning thirty times a second, six and a half thousand light-years away. Chinese astronomers wrote down its explosion in 1054.</span>
      <span class="ptm-room-tags"><em>time perception</em> · <em>rhythm</em></span>
    </span>
    <span class="ptm-room-state">scaffold</span>
  </div>

  <div class="ptm-room is-scaffold" aria-disabled="true">
    <span class="ptm-room-num">04</span>
    <span class="ptm-room-body">
      <span class="ptm-room-title">Biophilia</span>
      <span class="ptm-room-sub">Why a few plants on a desk drop a measurable amount of cortisol.</span>
      <span class="ptm-room-tags"><em>restorative environments</em> · <em>woodcut botanical</em></span>
    </span>
    <span class="ptm-room-state">scaffold</span>
  </div>

  <div class="ptm-room is-scaffold" aria-disabled="true">
    <span class="ptm-room-num">05</span>
    <span class="ptm-room-body">
      <span class="ptm-room-title">Umwelt</span>
      <span class="ptm-room-sub">A tick perceives three things. A mantis shrimp perceives sixteen color channels. What you see is a species-decision.</span>
      <span class="ptm-room-tags"><em>von Uexk&uuml;ll</em> · <em>field guide</em></span>
    </span>
    <span class="ptm-room-state">scaffold</span>
  </div>

  <div class="ptm-room is-scaffold" aria-disabled="true">
    <span class="ptm-room-num">06</span>
    <span class="ptm-room-body">
      <span class="ptm-room-title">Pareidolia</span>
      <span class="ptm-room-sub">A field of random ASCII. You will see faces in it. You are making the faces.</span>
      <span class="ptm-room-tags"><em>pattern completion</em> · <em>star-chart engraving</em></span>
    </span>
    <span class="ptm-room-state">scaffold</span>
  </div>

</nav>

<footer class="ptm-colophon">
  <p>This is a <em>local</em> exhibit. Each room is a single page, code-of-and-for the browser, gesturing toward another medium: paint chip, instrument panel, herbarium plate, field guide. The pointing is the point.</p>
